<problem>
<p>Given random variable \(X\) with following probability density function:</p>
<table style="border: 1px solid black">
    <tr>
      <th>\(x\)</th>
      <td>1</td> <td>2</td> <td>3</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>\(P(x)\)</th>
      <td>0.3</td> <td>0.5</td> <td>0.2</td>
    </tr>
  </table>

<ul><li>For \(Y=2^X\), what is \(E[Y]\), \(V(Y)\) and \(\sigma_Y\)?</li></ul>
<numericalresponse answer="4.2">
  <label>\(E[Y]\)</label>
<responseparam type="tolerance" default="0.001"/>
  <formulaequationinput />
    <solution>
    <div class="detailed-solution">
      <p>Explanation</p>
      <p> Calculate the value of Y for all possible x values </p>
      <p> \(E[Y]\) = (0.3*2) + (0.5*4) + (0.2*8) = 4.2 </p>
    </div>
  </solution>
</numericalresponse>
<numericalresponse answer="4.36">
  <label>\(V(Y)\)</label>
<responseparam type="tolerance" default="0.001"/>
  <formulaequationinput />
    <solution>
    <div class="detailed-solution">
      <p>Explanation</p>
      <p> \(V[Y]\) = E([Y - &#956;]<sup>2</sup>) where &#956; = 4.2 </p>
      <p> Simplifying it, \(V[Y]\) = 4.36 </p>
    </div>
  </solution>

</numericalresponse>
<numericalresponse answer="2.088">
  <label>\(\sigma_Y\)</label>
<responseparam type="tolerance" default="0.001"/>
  <formulaequationinput />
    <solution>
    <div class="detailed-solution">
      <p>Explanation</p>
      <p> \(\sigma_Y\) =  <math><msqrt><mi>(V(Y))</mi></msqrt></math> </p>
      <p> \(\sigma_Y\) = 2.088 </p>
    </div>
  </solution>
</numericalresponse>

<ul><li>If \(Z=aX+b\) with two constant \(a,b\in\mathbb{R}\), and \(E[Z]=0\), \(V(Z)=1\), what is \(a\) and \(b\)?</li></ul>
<numericalresponse answer="0.3674">
  <label>\(a\)</label>
<responseparam type="tolerance" default="0.001"/>
  <formulaequationinput />
    <solution>
    <div class="detailed-solution">
      <p>Explanation</p>
      <p> E(aX + b) = a*E(X) + b </p>
      <p> E(X) = 1.9 and thus, 1.9*a + b = 0 </p>
      <p> V(aX + b) = a<sup>2</sup>*V(X) + 0 as V(b) = 0 </p>
      <p> V(X) = 2.722 and thus, a<sup>2</sup>*2.722 = 1 </p>
      <p> Solving these equations, a = 0.3674 and b = -0.6980 </p>
    </div>
  </solution>
</numericalresponse>
<numericalresponse answer="-0.6980">
  <label>\(b\)</label>
<responseparam type="tolerance" default="0.001"/>
  <formulaequationinput />
</numericalresponse>

</problem>